The article is a transcript of remarks made by Vice President Mike Pence during the swearing-in ceremony of David Friedman as the 20th United States Ambassador to Israel. Pence highlights President Trump's commitment to Israel and the Jewish people, and praises Friedman's qualifications and dedication to the relationship between the US and Israel. Friedman expresses his gratitude and promises to work towards promoting peace and stability in the Middle East. He also acknowledges the support of his family and friends.